Denagamage Praboth Mahela de Silva Jayawardene (born 27 May 1977),
known as Mahela Jayawardene,
is a Sri Lankan cricket coach and former cricketer. He is regarded as one of the modern greats of batsmanship,
especially due to his mastery of playing spin bowling.
Jayawardene's highest test score, 374 against South Africa is the highest test score 
by a right handed batsman in the history of test cricket.